  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "Finding \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo can be a bit more challenging since these platforms primarily showcase active campaigns. However, there are several strategies you can use to discover upcoming projects:\n\n### Kickstarter\n\n1. **Follow Creators:** Sometimes creators announce their upcoming projects on their Kickstarter profile or through their social media channels. Follow your favorite creators to get updates.\n\n2. **Kickstarter Newsletter:** Sign up for Kickstarter's newsletter. They occasionally feature upcoming projects and provide insights into what\u2019s coming next.\n\n3. **Social Media:** Follow Kickstarter on platforms like Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram. They often tease upcoming projects and highlight creators about to launch new campaigns.\n\n4. **Community Boards:** Browse Kickstarter\u2019s community forums where creators might talk about their upcoming projects to gather interest and feedback before launching.\n\n### Indiegogo\n\n1. **Pre-Launch Pages:** Indiegogo allows creators to set up pre-launch pages called \"Coming Soon\" pages. These pages can be featured on Indiegogo\u2019s main site or found through searches. Creators use these pages to build email lists and share updates.\n\n2. **Indiegogo Newsletter:** Subscribe to Indiegogo\u2019s newsletter. They highlight new and upcoming campaigns and sometimes tease upcoming projects.\n\n3. **Indiegogo Explore Section:** Indiegogo has a section for trending campaigns. Sometimes, creators announce pre-launch campaigns within this same community space. \n\n4. **Social Media:** Follow Indiegogo on their social media channels for announcements and teasers about upcoming projects.\n\n### General Tips\n\n1. **Creator Social Media:** Many project creators announce upcoming launches on their personal or business social media profiles. Following them can give you early access or sneak peeks.\n\n2. **Industry Blogs and News:** Websites and blogs focused on crowdfunding often feature articles about upcoming campaigns. Keeping track of these can give you insights on what\u2019s coming.\n\n3. **Networking:** Join relevant groups or forums like those on Reddit or Facebook that focus on crowdfunding. These communities often discuss and share information about upcoming projects.\n\nBy using these methods, you can stay ahead of the curve and discover forthcoming Kickstarter and Indiegogo projects before they launch.",
